        "title": "Java ReentrantLock issue",
        "body": "<p>Hello I'm having some issues regarding <code>Lock's implementation: ReentrantLock<\/code>. I'm using a <code>singleton cache<\/code> inside <code>Spring 3.0(web)<\/code>. However when I open several browser tabs at the exact same time, all threads seem to lock, and I get several unnecesary web service calls. Why is this? isn't <code>lock.tryLock()<\/code> thread safe?.\nI've tried using an <code>atomic boolean<\/code> instead and the problem persisted.\nI also checked the same instance of Cache is referenced.  <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.util.List;\nimport java.util.concurrent.locks.Lock;\nimport java.util.concurrent.locks.ReentrantLock;\n\npublic class SomeCache {\n\n    private List&lt;Object&gt; stuff;\n    private Lock lock;\n\n    public SomeCache() { \n        lock = new ReentrantLock();\n    }\n\n    public List&lt;Object&gt; getStuff() { \n        if(lock.tryLock()) {\n            try{ \n                //call webService\n            }\n            finally { \n                 lock.unlock(); \n            } \n        }\n        else {\n           //get other data\n        }\n        return stuff;\n    }\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Thanks in advance, cheers.<\/p>\n",
